article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- — Hunter Sallis had 22 points, seven rebounds and four assists and Wake Forest defeated Clemson 81-76 in a regular-season finale on Saturday night. Andrew Carr scored 12 of his 17 points and Efton Reid all 12 of his in the second half for Demon Deacons (19-12, 11-9 ACC), who snapped a three-game losing streak. Cameron Hildreth added 11 points and seven rebounds. The Deacons shot 58%. PJ Hall scored 16 of his 18 points and Chase Hunter 15 of his 17 in the second half for the Tigers (21-10, 11-9). Joseph Girard III added 14 points and Jack Clark 10. Clemson shot 46% overall but was over 58% in the second half. An 8-0 run midway through the second half capped by Reid's 3-pointer, just his seventh of the season, put Wake Forest up for good, The Deacons didn't secure the victory until Sallis and Kevin Miller made two free throws each in the final 10 seconds. Wake Forest started the second half making only 3 of 10 shots in giving up a 34-28 halftime lead but then hit 12 shots in a row over the final 11 minutes, only missing its final attempt. The Demon Deacons scored the last seven points of the half to take their six-point halftime lead behind 15 points by Sallis. Wake Forest shot 52% in the first half while Clemson only shot 38%. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
